Place cut vegetables in a large bowl and drizzle with olive oil then season with salt and pepper. Toss until well mixed. Place into a grill basket. Cook pasta according to directions on package; keep warm. Cook vegetables on grill over medium-high heat, stirring frequently, until vegetables are crisp tender and slightly charred. Cooking time will vary between 10-20 minutes depending on grill used. Remove from grill; keep warm. Toss pasta, veggies and tomatoes until well combined. Top with Parmesan cheese and a sprinkle of fresh ground pepper.